  "datePublished": "2026-04-02",
  "description": "Annual herb from Tropaeolaceae, domesticated in the Andes. Entirely edible leaves and flowers with glucosinolate-derived peppery flavor; unripe immature seeds develop as \"poor man's capers.\" Premier trap crop for aphids (Aphididae), with volatile emissions attracting and confusing Aphis fabae, Aphis gossypii; feeding preference diverts pest pressure from adjacent crops. Herbaceous annual vine 1.5-3 m depending on cultivar and support.",
  "name": "Tropaeolum majus",
